title: Reapply for your driving licence if you've been disqualified

heading_context: Reapply for your driving licence if you've been disqualified
chunks.html_content:
You must apply for a new licence to drive again if:

  • you’ve been disqualified from driving
  • your provisional or full driving licence has been cancelled (‘revoked’)

heading_context: Reapply for your driving licence if you've been disqualified
Disqualification for drink or drug driving
chunks.html_content:
You can reapply for your provisional or full driving licence before your disqualification period ends.

DVLA will send you a D27 renewal form:

  • 56 days before your disqualification ends
  • 90 days before your disqualification ends if you’re a high risk offender

Fill in the form and send it to DVLA with the driving licence fee. You’ll be told if you need to send a new passport-style photo in the D27 renewal form.

If you do not get your renewal form in the post, you can get one from the Post Office.

To renew your licence for:

  • a car or motorcycle use form D1
  • a lorry or bus use form D2

heading_context: Reapply for your driving licence if you've been disqualified
Disqualification for drink or drug driving
chunks.html_content: You cannot drive until your disqualification period is over.

heading_context: Reapply for your driving licence if you've been disqualified
chunks.html_content:
You must apply for a new provisional licence and retake both parts of your driving test if your licence is cancelled within 2 years of passing them.

If your licence is cancelled you can apply for a new one at any time. Get form D1 from the Post Office. Send it with the fee to the address on the form.
chunks.plain_content:

New drivers
You must apply for a new provisional licence and retake both parts of your driving test if your licence is cancelled within 2 years of passing them.
If your licence is cancelled you can apply for a new one at any time. Get form D1 from the Post Office. Send it with the fee to the address on the form.

heading_context: Reapply for your driving licence if you've been disqualified
chunks.html_content: You must retake both parts of your driving test if your provisional licence is cancelled after you’ve passed your test, but you have not sent off for your full licence yet. You can use your current provisional licence to take the tests.
chunks.plain_content:
Reapply for your driving licence if you've been disqualified
Provisional licence holders
You must retake both parts of your driving test if your provisional licence is cancelled after you’ve passed your test, but you have not sent off for your full licence yet. You can use your current provisional licence to take the tests.

heading_context: Reapply for your driving licence if you've been disqualified
Failing to hand over your licence to court
chunks.html_content:
You must apply for a new licence if your licence is invalid because you did not hand it over to the court for endorsement.

Get form D1 or D2 from the Post Office. Send it with the driving licence fee to the address on the form.

To renew your licence for:

  • a car or motorcycle use form D1
  • a lorry or bus use form D2

heading_context: Reapply for your driving licence if you've been disqualified
chunks.html_content:
Contact the Driver and Vehicle Agency (DVA) if you’re in Northern Ireland.

DVLA will return your licence when your disqualification period ends.
